<h2 id="editors-notes">Editor‚Äôs notes</h2>

<p>Hey friends! In this lesson I‚Äôll show you 12 very common ways the A-major chord can be modified to slightly change up the sound. I‚Äôll break down common variations such as Asus2, Asus4, A7, Amaj7, and A/C#‚Ä¶ in addition to showing some ways to change up your finger positions to make other variations possible as well (e.g., playing it with a single finger barred on the 2nd fret). Overall, my hope is to demystify many of these common voicings ‚Äì so that the next time you run into them, you‚Äôll be ready.</p>

